# 4) Content scope issues (important credibility corrections)

## 4.1 “70% OWASP coverage” is risky unless you prove it

If you claim “70% coverage”, security reviewers will ask:

*   which OWASP list?
*   mapping table?
*   evidence?

You do have a whole “OWASP coverage section” — that’s good.  
But it currently contains:

*   bold marketing claim in hero **and** again later
*   “Coming Soon platform will address these 3 risks…”

This creates expectation debt and procurement questions.

### Recommendation

*   Remove OWASP claim from hero.
*   Keep OWASP mapping as a separate “Security coverage” section **but present it as**:
    *   “Addresses the following risk categories”
    *   “Coverage depends on configuration”
    *   “See docs for mapping”

That’s Cloudflare style: bounded + link to evidence.

***

## 4.2 Your “SDK Status & Roadmap” section reads too detailed for landing page

“15 weeks development • Q2-Q3 2026 release” will make enterprise visitors think:

*   “small team”
*   “uncertain”

### Better landing-page version

Replace that entire section with:

*   “Language support” (TS / Python)
*   “Supported providers”
*   “Release notes / changelog link”

Keep the timeline in GitHub or docs.

